Comment:
*Spoilers ahead*







I can‚Äôt believe she switched personality from her in-book personality. In the book she felt sacrifices were necessary for the good of the Empire, but the moment  her home (Which in the book she said was the Empire, like her father) was threatened she flips over like she never had any attachment or loyalty to Palpatine.

And all because the writer said she ‚ÄúDidn‚Äôt want to write about a nazi character.‚Äù.

???....Then why the fuck did you let them advertise your story as one?! Or let the author of the prequel depict her so differently from your character?

I liked the game don‚Äôt get me wrong, but I was so excited to finally have an imperial perspective. What you see of her in this trailer, is the majority of her imperial scenes, I just can‚Äôt believe it. We have enough rebellion stories to fill several libraries, now we still need a real imperial, not someone who abandoned their principals the moment danger arises. It‚Äôs so funny that the book ended with her promising her mother Zeehay that she was not a traitor....Yet this story is about her doing everything the opposite.

I want a character with a strong will and faith in their beliefs, she turned out a lot weaker willed than I thought she had been in the book. (And she is a tough person in the book.)

Please let Battlefront 3 let us finally have a real imperial view, or atleast a separatist one..

This line and the scene in which it is said NEVER appear in the game.  

Someone should sue EA for false advertising. They lied to our faces and expected to get away with it.

Title: Star Wars Battlefront II: Full Length Reveal Trailer
Comment:
The campaign is a huge letdown if you wanted a true story from the other side, akin to Thrawn, the Inferno squad book and the original swbf2 campaign. *Spoilers*

The first few missions are great, but it falls apart very quickly. Instead of showing a vengeful imperial fighting to keep the empire alive like this trailer shows us, she switches sides. She goes from a die hard Imperial to a full on rebel freedom fighter in one cutscene. The problem is that her character has been developed as a believer in the ideals of the empire, even during the cinder mission she says that the empire is supposed to be protecting the civilians. It made sense she would try to stop operation cinder, but it makes no sense that she joins the rebels. It would've been better that she joins another Imperial faction she believes to be better, not to go full fucking rebel.

Title: Star Wars Battlefront II: Full Length Reveal Trailer
Comment:
I don't get why Disney nuked the EU in favor of this garbage. Kasan Moor, Callista, and Lumiya are three perfectly good examples of side characters that could have been brought to the spotlight with their own videogame. Its like they didn't even know about Mara Jade or Jaina Solo. Can you believe that there are people that say that Disney's Star Wars is better because it has more female lead characters. When someone told me that I thought, REALLY??!!! You probably don't even know which content is part of the Legends continuity. 

The main reason Disney fails at bringing original quality content is because they decided to nuke the EU. Everything has already been done in the Expanded Universe, everything that Disney creates will be rehash after rehash. This is simply a going to be a retelling of Lumiya's story. Just like how TFA was a retelling of The Original Trilogy and Rogue One was a rehash of the first level of Dark Forces. Hate me all you want, but this not so "unified canon" is one big failed rehash. 

Anyways "new" fans, keep sheeping along, just like the rest of pop culture, I'll be back here with the truth just like the rest of us original Star Wars fans, those of us that lived it before it was mainstream. Darn Disney, making me mad, I could Spit! xD 

Have a nice day and keep the REAL Star Wars alive.

Title: Star Wars Battlefront II: Full Length Reveal Trailer
Comment:
This is just hype. Do you guys remember "No Man's Sky"? I see that happening again. 

Let's be honest here - there was nothing wrong with the Battlefront series to begin with. At least, nothing too awful anyway - no game is perfect. 

Look at what happened when they tried to "fix" those problems - less than good flying mechanics, sporadic fire without much sense where the projectiles were going to hit, and a lack of a "class" system involving more customization. 

Good problems to fix, and instead they creating dozens more, and didn't even fix the sporadic fire issue. The new class system was sub-optimal, and the flying mechanics weren't that much better, either.

What do you think they're going to do with this one? Not a whole lot, I can see. I sense a trap - one that costs about ‚Ç¨50, and isn't going to please many people.

Title: Star Wars Battlefront II: Full Length Reveal Trailer
Comment:
Well...well...well...
The game has surely become better BUT... I might have some MAJOR suggestions.

1: The hero system... Heroes are great...for real but they can become a pain in the ass. You can use a hero once you have 5000 points and just roll out. Well... it is something but not good. Heroes should be obtainable but not that easily. In the old Battlefront 2 you got heroes for a specific streak. It could be much better than the current system. I admit that it is very hard to solve but the hero unlocks MUST BE BALANCED. In Battlefront (2015) your team got 100% fucked up if the enemy team got 3 heroes at once. Just don't make the same mistake again.

2: The number of them... I understand that there will be many heroes in the game but the numbers of them shouldn't be above 1... Every map would have a specific playable hero or the other solution could be not letting a second hero deploy if there is already one out there. 

3: This is more like a thorn in the eye... Why did you let this happen? The characters of different eras fight each other... I personally don't like it.... not at all... Darth Maul VS Rey... nahnahnah... don't go too far kid... The heroes you can choose on the map should be depending on which era you are playing in... Separatists VS the Republic would mean NO Luke Skywalker nor grown up Boda Fett...Rey...Han Solo and so on... You have many heroes to choose from... General Grievous...Obi-Wan...Jedi Anakin...Yoda...Dooku... Don't mess it up... It would make many players happier when they join the battle.

If they don't read comments like this on YouTube where should I contact them then? :D

Thanks for reading this! I would love to see your opinions on this case.

Title: Star Wars Battlefront II: Full Length Reveal Trailer
Comment:
"All eras"? I only counted 4 out of 7 or 8 (in regards to the number of fan favorites.)

The game looks great and completely amazing (hope EA doesn't screw it up) but it would be nice if they were to add some of the Legends era also

In fact, I compiled a list of eras that are already and should be added in the game since the first trailer, as follow.

Already in the game (in chronological order):

1.) Pre-Clone Wars (Episode 1) *Guessing since Maul had his old robes and saber still*
2.) The Clone Wars (Episode 2 -3)
3.) Galactic civil War (Episode 3 - Rouge One - Episode 4 - 6)
4.) New Republic/First Order (Episode 6 - 8)

Eras that should also be added to the game (Also in chronological order.)

1.) The Old Republic (4000 - 1000 BBY)
*Episode 1 - 6*
2.) The Thrawn Crisis (9 - 10 ABY) *If the canon doesn't alter the timeline further then it already has)
*Episode 7 - 9*
3.) Yuuzang Vong War (25 - 29 ABY)
4.) The Sith-Imperial War (127 - 138 ABY)

I really hope the creators consider these options.

Title: Star Wars Battlefront II: Full Length Reveal Trailer
Comment:
I'm glad they're actually giving it a story and some substance this go around, as the series deserves it. But I am slightly disappointed the Story seems to take place right after episode 6 (I could be wrong but the only suggestion of the Clone Wars era was Yoda and Darth Maul, and that's almost guaranteed to be MP only.) I'd love to see a tiered story line that starts from the Clone Wars and up to the First Order, rather than jump right into the remnants of the Empire and probably end right as the First Order gains its power. 

As hated as the Prequels are, the Clone Wars had excellent potential for stories, both for the Jedi and just as Clone Troopers. Plus even for Multiplayer you could add a ton of Jedi that got more character building in the EU (even if 90% of that was thrown away after disney took over.) I'd love to see a match between Plo Koon and Darth Maul or Kit Fisto versus Sidious (other than the disappointing 5 seconds in Episode 3.) 

The game does look significantly better than the last one, so I'll probably get it and hope like hell EA doesn't disappoint me again.

Title: Star Wars Battlefront II: Full Length Reveal Trailer
Comment:
Excellent trailer. I would be excited if I didn't know I was being deceived. It is a regular occurrence and current trend for triple A games to promise the world, only for us to find out on release that they severely lack the features purported and fail to meet our expectations. I must confess they have broken my spirit. I was once a wide eyed naive young 40something, who believed the promises of large game developers, but alas I shall be fooled no more.
As you may have guessed I am an optimist and sorely await the day when battlefront would return to its former glory. I need not describe my dismay at the release of Battlefront 1 (2015), for we all felt it. But I do hold hope for the future. But as so clearly stated, "hope cannot save them", so retire now I shall, cry myself to sleep I must.

Title: Star Wars Battlefront II: Full Length Reveal Trailer
Comment:
Dear EA, 
    I don't care if this trailer was made in the game's engine.  I could not care less how the game looks, so long as the graphics do not take away from the overall experience.  I don't care how good the trailer looks, because I'm not buying a trailer, and I'm not buying a movie either for that matter.  I'm (potentially) buying a game, but before making such a decision, I need to be informed on whether or not the actual experience of the game, that is to say the gameplay, is to my liking.  A cinematic trailer does not inform me about the substance of the actual product, and certainly not about what is presumably it's main selling point.  A trailer like this one does not convince me to buy your game, nor does it get me in any way hyped.  I'll admit that this trailer appears to hint at the game's story, but the problem for you is this:  I never played the original games for the story, I did not play the previous Battlefront for the story, and (if I play it at all) I will most certainly not play this game for the story.  A bit of constructive criticism:  if you want to sell your product, advertise the product itself.  I think it may be time for a change in your marketing strategy, as advertising a game in a way that avoids showing gameplay makes me think that the gameplay is not worth showing (and in 2015, that was the case).  
    
    Sincerely, a (very) irritated fan.

Title: Star Wars Battlefront II: Full Length Reveal Trailer
Comment:
Yeah, there's definitely going to be a lot of old school star wars video game fans or general EA haters in this comment section, so...warning.

Anyway, from what I've seen. I'm totally stoked for this! Not because it's a Star Wars game, but mainly because it looks like the criticisms from the previous game are going to be acknowledged and improved upon. We're getting a single player campaign, one that takes place between Return of the Jedi and the Force Awakens, and it has you playing as a normal soldier (okay, special forces, but still, not a jedi) in the Empire (the bad guys). Not only that, but the multiplayer modes seem to really expand on the star wars saga, with characters from the prequels, the originals, and the new movies.

Although I enjoy playing Battlefront, I will admit that having nothing but multiplayer made it repetitive, there weren't enough maps or variations, and the process of increasing your ranking is frustrating and long. I'm just hoping that this game gives us big battles with many battlefields, while also making sure everybody (pro or not) is able to access a variety of weapons and customization options much more easily. (A simple fix would be having a collection of weapons and gear available for purchase, but you have to level up to access another tear. Don't make it so that each weapon has to have a specific rank before buying it.)

Title: Star Wars Battlefront II: Full Length Reveal Trailer
Comment: Nothing wrong with female protagonists but I think people's "bullshit" meter is filling up to the brim. Female fighters and strong women exist in real life of course but in the media we've had so many ass kicking females in places you'd usually see a male in, in such a short space of time, it's turning into a cliche gimmick and people are reacting. Me personally I have no problem playing as a female character but Star Wars is such a huge franchise and gaming is more immersive than watching a movie, we like to project ourselves into a character and it's been so, so long since we, as Star Wars fans have had the opportunity to play a Star Wars video game with a full campaign story, and we're forced to play as this imperial female character who looks like her own person and will make decisions for us. I think it would've been wise to allow us to choose to create our own main protagonist, so we can all see ourselves in this next gen Star Wars campaign that we rarely ever get.

Title: Star Wars Battlefront II: Full Length Reveal Trailer
Comment:
While it's good that DICE listened to fan feeback such as the want for a single player campaign and space battles, I can't help to feel like they mess with the formula too much. Why just 40 players on the ground and 25 in space battles? And why won't we be able to board battleships and take them out from the inside, just like the old battlefront II? And why not galactic conquest? What is so hard to understand about just giving the fans what they want?

If I had a say for the game, I would want to see seamless transition from ground to space (like Free Radicals version of Battlefront 3), in which all the old features would be present. To make up for the large scale to fight on, I would like to see maybe 100 players per server. One game mode could be something like: The Republic have to destroy the CIS base on the ground, while the CIS have to destroy the Republics capital ship in space. That would offer some cool strategic thinking in terms of when to attack and when to defend, and how a team would choose to plan for and compose the overall army. Add the meta game of the galactic conquest to the mix and you have a full on strategy experience on top of all that, kind of like what the Total War series is doing, and you would have not only a game that the fans would love to play, but that is also differentiated from the battlefield series.

That said, my opinion when watching the original Star Wars films was that the Empire was an elitist ruling government (especially with their likeness to Nazis) and I imagined them to only have male white humans in positions of power. And this is fine since they were villainous space racists and were portrayed as the bad guys, whilst the light side of the force consisted of people and aliens of all shapes and sizes. The message here being, that the foreword thinking and diverse good guys defeated the oppressive racist villains. Now introducing a mixed race female character as a storm trooper kind of undermines this message.

Title: Star Wars Battlefront II: Full Length Reveal Trailer
Comment:
Huh, a singleplayer story from the Imperial perspective and after the death of the Emperor at the Battle of Endor to boot.

Colour me interested ... and that's saying something because otherwise this game wouldn't be on my radar at all, same as the first one from DICE. Still not a fan at all from overpowered Hero characters in MP so unless that aspect changes dramatically that'll weigh in significantly as a downside.

I'm somewhat missing a nice Star Wars singleplayer. Had been looking very much forward for 1313 and my hopes for a renewal of the KotoR have been dashed along the rumours by BioWare.

If DICE were to decide making a singleplayer (possibly add a cooperative campaign as MP component) epic, oh boy would I be hardpressed finding things that might turn me down from a purchase. Something like the old T.I.E. Fighter, in Frostbyte engine ... damn son, my wallet would be open faster than Solo's Kessel run.

Comment:
Alright time to answer some peoples questions

1. No you can't change the main characters' gender. Why? Because it's a canon story with a canon character.

2. On the panel and their website space battles are confirmed but it's still unclear if they will function in the same way as SWBF2

3. On the panel they showed concept art of clonetroopers on Kamino.

4. Website features picture of a clanker(TCW fans will understand)

5. Panel and website confirms 4 classes Assault, Heavy, Officer and    Specialist

6. Panel confirms more in depth customization of not only soldiers but heroes aswell

7. An article published on Mashup the creative director said no Season Pass for this type of game.

Title: Star Wars Battlefront II: Full Length Reveal Trailer
Comment:
Hear me out,

I think it would be cool if they improved sky battles by making the flight controls more complicated as well as having the mode assign us certain fighters with certain objectives and squads. 

For example A-Wings would all have a certain objective different from the Y-Wing and X-Wing objectives. They would also follow under their own respected squad leaders;
(A-Wing: "Red Leader", X-Wing: "Blue Leader", Y-Wing "Gold Leader" etc.)

An example of this could be like, in walker assault (add more than to walkers at a time) the Snow Speeders could attack the AT-ATs at all times but target different parts of the body (legs) to make the walker fall. The squad leaders could set objectives that the rest of the squad could follow like "Aim for the front left leg!", requiring team work. Due to the hopefully more complex flying mechanics, it would be more of a challenge to get objectives done and require more actual skill to pilot.

This could run somewhat like Battlefield's squad system. also the B-Wing should be flyable and we should be able to dispatch from carrier ships like the Star Destroyer.

Same thing goes for the Imperials, I want vehicles to be kinda unlockable by rank. That way only the best players have access to fighters like the Tie Interceptor and Tie Bomber as well as squad leader vehicles for the Rebel Alliance.

Also, accidentally flying into an ally should cause death for both.

There should be a somewhat hardcore mode as well for all game modes, Friendly fire, First person locked (aircraft as well).

Title: Star Wars Battlefront II: Full Length Reveal Trailer
Comment: You know, I bought the first game without realising that the local coop (and pure single player) options were so bad. I don't play games online but I loved the original Battlefront games because I had so much fun with my friends fighting together against the other side. The remake was (frankly) terrible for people who play local. The graphics and audio were outstanding but the game got boring really quickly (I definitely clocked less than ten hours in total). Does anyone know if this sequel will actually have couch coop? I know they've said there's a single player campaign but battlefront 2 had galactic conquest, a campaign which could be played coop and endless skirmishes that could be played with or against your friends. That was great content right there.

Title: Star Wars Battlefront II: Full Length Reveal Trailer
Comment:
I hope that there'll be more content than the first game like these:

> Customizable option's such as putting further details on your character (putting on decal's/emblems on every era of soldiers (including droids), customizing eye color, hair, facial details etc.) 

> Actual Space Battle's where you can destroy a enemy flagship from the outside or go into the ship and destroy its internal system's, ship customization would be cool as well. 

> Multiple offline modes (split-screen for each) with (won't happen more than likely) a Galactic Conquest type mode where you can take over a galaxy (planet by planet), select what planets you want to play skirmish battles on, with each team having a certain amount of ticket's and capturing points on the map, A hero vs villain's mode where each side has a certain amount of tickets. 

> More content for online, (no more stupid gap filling modes like the first game) maybe a Operation's type of game mode like in Bf1 where you jump from multiple planets to fall back to, that would be perfect. Possibly the Galactic Conquest type mode I mentioned earlier, but you can play online with friends. Return of walker assault where it's Clones vs Droids where the Clones have AT-TE's and the Clones have to destroy the Droids transport that they need to get off the planet. Or maybe even a online conquest type mode like Battlefield has, where each team has to capture points and only has a certain amount of tickets to do it (As listed above, but online). 

> A campaign for each era from a soldier's point of view (maybe DICE and EA could make a Add-On for that for a reasonable price if not included in the game already). 

But that's about all I can think of to make this game great, but overall I'm kinda looking forward to the game. But I'm still going to wait for reviews until I buy the actual game.

Comment:
Right. I thought it necessary for me to write this. Give this game a chance for god sake! It looks amazing from this trailer. I'm counting on the fact EA have learnt from their mistakes from the first game (which was a decent game, just lacked content). For all those still whining, here is a list of official details EA have released so far :1. All out space battles with flag ships2. All 3 eras3. class system reinstated 4. Customisable Heroes with their abilities !!5. Campaign 6. offline skirmish mode against bots7. No season pass!! ( but they have something else in mind) 8. Lots of upcoming free content and maps 9. New array of customisable characters for each class and also customisable vehicles10. Brand new heroes ! 
They've listened to our feedback and trust me, that is something big for EA to do. Wait for the gameplay trailers and some clone wars videos, then we can make some assumptions. For now, just go with it guys, it's STAR WARS for crying out loud!

Title: Star Wars Battlefront II: Full Length Reveal Trailer
Comment:
If you ask me, I get the feeling that EA was just getting their feet wet in the Star Wars Universe. They gave us a taste of what their take on the Star Wars Universe is, what with the Frostbite Engine and all, and we were very much impressed. I mean, let's face facts guys. Sure they may have screwed us over by making us pay for extra DLC; sure they may have lacked in a whole bunch of heroes and troopers and whatnot -- but let's face it, it was made pretty damn well. Don't deny it. You know you enjoyed flying an X-Wing against the Imperial Walkers.

The Engine was nifty, the combat system was neat, the graphics and visuals were amazing, and the gameplay in general was pretty darn satisfying. Now they've announced Battlefront 2, which also sounds and looks freaking amazing. But why so soon? The first one was released just two years ago, and now we're already getting bombarded by all this new and amazing stuff.

Well, like I said above: EA were just getting their feet wet. Essentially, they were just giving us a taste of the potential that they have to make a great Star Wars game, and at the end of the day, they delivered. Not only that, but they learnt from what they've done wrong, and have listened to their fans to deliver the next best thing. Star Wars Battlefront 2 **is** the Star Wars Battlefront we were promised. SWB1 was just a taste. A test. An experiment. And we played our parts brilliantly, because now EA has listened.

Now, you can either sit here and whinge over EA and their "money-grabbing schemes", or you can admire the effort they've gone to into making this such a good game.

Needless to say, I'm excited for it. I'll probably wait for a month or two before I preorder it, or until the Beta (if any) comes out, but I'll most definitely get it.

That's why it had less than 10% of the population of PS4 users on the PC, for example.  There was also incredibly poor weapon balance, with the more expensive digital version of the game coming with a far superior weapon (dl-44) than what everyone else started with.

Bad weapon balance, forced to play with foreigners with high lag without a server browser to allow you to pick who to play against.  Unless something changes drastically from the last one, this will be another waste of money.  And after wasting my money on the last game, I won't be quick to pre-order this one.

Title: Star Wars Battlefront II: Full Length Reveal Trailer
Comment:
For anyone that didn't go to the website for details, here's a brief summary.

Pros
-This will include a single player campaign. (A bad-ass empire one at that)
-Multiplayer will now feature classes, vehicles, and ALL ERAS. 
-Space Battles are now once again a thing.
-Heroes will be available from every era (Cross your fingers for Jar-Jar DLC) 
-Split Screen Co-Op 
-Larger customization 

Cons (So Far)
-Battles will still be relatively small in comparison to previous titles. (40 player combat, 24 player space combat)
-Older game modes related to the Battlefront series haven't been confirmed (Unlikely to be)
-Micro-transactions almost certainly confirmed (Case-key style system likely, and not just for cosmetics)
-Pre-ordering the special edition still gives the player some-what of an advantage (Unclear how large the advantage)

Points of interest 
-Space battles (Unclear if they will be as the previous battlefront titles had them or if this'll just be Battlefront's fighter mode in a space setting)
-Servers (Unclear if this'll still be peer-to-peer connection or dedicated servers, guessing by the scale of the multiplayer battles it's very likely peer-to-peer)
-Micro-transactions (You know why)

For the most part DICE has listened. Now let's all cross our fingers EA doesn't shit on our dreams, and remember kids no matter what don't hop on the hype train it could get real shaky towards the end.

1. Offline Mode
2. Single player story (check)
3. Galactic Mode
4. To be able to play with bots for practice and sense the internet is horrible where I live so online mode is not always an option.

Please don't preorder guys until we have all the details and some game-play footage with decent reviews so we can get away from the preordering culture.
